Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Thailand  trading. (SET)  Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 12:30 p.m. lunch break in
Bangkok.  The SET Index fell 0.3 percent to 1,025.63.  Capital Nomura Securities Pcl (CNS)  : The stock brokerage
rose 0.9 percent to 28.25 baht, headed for its biggest gain
since Dec. 9. The company denied media reports that it was in
talks with a potential business partner, Capital Nomura said in
a statement released during the trading break, without
specifying the source of the speculation.  Khon Kaen Sugar Industry Pcl (KSL)   rose 1.5 percent to
13.2 baht, poised for its biggest gain in a week. The company
said annual net income jumped more than 11-fold to 1.9 billion
baht ($60 million).  Property Perfect Pcl (PF)  , a property developer,
increased 1.5 percent to 0.69 baht, headed for the sharpest gain
in more than a week. The company offered to buy the shares it
